    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>In the following reaction ' $C$ ' is an aromatic compound having substitutents $D$ and $E$. What are $D$ and $E$ ?</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2023 (Online) 13th May Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 9 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mkfg6t7j/cc2cb173-e4d6-4768-935f-bfb365287d8f/cc670ef0-f210-11f0-aa7a-bbc1e273ac26/file-jaoe38c1mkfg6t7k.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mkfg6t7j/cc2cb173-e4d6-4768-935f-bfb365287d8f/cc670ef0-f210-11f0-aa7a-bbc1e273ac26/file-jaoe38c1mkfg6t7k.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>",
