    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>(i), (ii) 2-hexanone undergoes haloform reaction to form bromoform and a carboxylate ion. This carboxylate ion undergoes hydrolysis to give pentanoic acid.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 2 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mnbw59wi/4ce36428-1600-474c-80ff-25ce3ca27081/b7490420-2b80-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw59wj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mnbw59wi/4ce36428-1600-474c-80ff-25ce3ca27081/b7490420-2b80-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw59wj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 2 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mnbw5act/80f3b3b9-9c87-4058-a09c-9e70f22cc136/b7a295d0-2b80-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw5acu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mnbw5act/80f3b3b9-9c87-4058-a09c-9e70f22cc136/b7a295d0-2b80-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw5acu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 2 English Explanation 3\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mnbw5aqi/080e235f-06b8-4166-bcda-b3a3f063c095/b7edcfa0-2b80-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw5aqj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mnbw5aqi/080e235f-06b8-4166-bcda-b3a3f063c095/b7edcfa0-2b80-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw5aqj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>(iii), (iv) Pentanoic acid react with bromine In presence of red-phosphorus to give $\\alpha$-bromocarboxylic acid. This reaction is Hell-Volhard-Zelinsky reaction.</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{COOH} \\xrightarrow[\\text { (iv) } \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}]{\\text { (iii) Red } \\mathrm{Br}_2} $$</p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 2 English Explanation 4\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mnbw7y3t/e0e54f38-6d46-4882-82d0-bda49cd8f19b/01998590-2b81-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw7y3u.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mnbw7y3t/e0e54f38-6d46-4882-82d0-bda49cd8f19b/01998590-2b81-11f1-9b76-91a623d95264/file-jaoe38c1mnbw7y3u.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\">",
