    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which of the following set of compounds react with $\\mathrm{NaHCO}_3$ ?</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 4 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w93v/c05716e3-fa6e-4f10-81b4-38c7a00d38db/5a8d1eb0-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w93w.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w93v/c05716e3-fa6e-4f10-81b4-38c7a00d38db/5a8d1eb0-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w93w.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>I, II, III, IV</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>I, II, III only</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>III, IV only</p>\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>I, III, IV only</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Phenol are weaker acid than carboxylic acids. So, phenolic -OH group does not react with $\\mathrm{NaHCO}_3$. Carboxylic acids react with $\\mathrm{NaHCO}_3$ to give brisk effervescences of carbon dioxide gas.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 4 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w5di/df01ee5b-5053-4754-97d8-0a336a79082b/57ab0d60-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w5dj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w5di/df01ee5b-5053-4754-97d8-0a336a79082b/57ab0d60-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w5dj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 4 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w6ka/1536316d-7039-460b-a92e-dea0886a10ad/589609a0-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w6kb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w6ka/1536316d-7039-460b-a92e-dea0886a10ad/589609a0-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w6kb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 4 English Explanation 3\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w7dz/e68ff568-0328-4edc-a4d7-b6af36490048/59394e80-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w7e0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w7dz/e68ff568-0328-4edc-a4d7-b6af36490048/59394e80-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w7e0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 19th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 4 English Explanation 4\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w8c5/04aafb5b-a7d2-4e16-b756-33d5a5342871/59f4d650-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w8c6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmx2w8c5/04aafb5b-a7d2-4e16-b756-33d5a5342871/59f4d650-235b-11f1-98be-2f5dfd4c42ac/file-jaoe38c1mmx2w8c6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>Hence, compounds III and IV only react with $\\mathrm{NaHCO}_3$.</p>",
