    "explanation": "<p>$n$-alcohol on reaction with hydrohalide gives alkyl halide. Further, reaction of alkyl halide with KCN followed by hydrolysis leads to formation of acid which have 1 carbon atom more than parent compound. The reaction involved is as follows</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 18th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 6 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmrrsp8t/b1540c5a-310e-455b-8efc-3d14be59cce8/081cd7d0-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrsp8u.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmrrsp8t/b1540c5a-310e-455b-8efc-3d14be59cce8/081cd7d0-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrsp8u.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 18th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 6 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmrrspmz/b03eb54b-56d4-4222-83f0-5f591646822d/086aa9b0-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrspn0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmrrspmz/b03eb54b-56d4-4222-83f0-5f591646822d/086aa9b0-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrspn0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 18th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 6 English Explanation 3\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmrrspyy/a92873de-4691-4353-9118-12a873c322df/08ac6da0-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrspyz.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmrrspyy/a92873de-4691-4353-9118-12a873c322df/08ac6da0-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrspyz.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 18th July Evening Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 6 English Explanation 4\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmrrsqci/7212cbc9-531f-4410-a10f-243736beef1e/08f6e420-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrsqcj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmrrsqci/7212cbc9-531f-4410-a10f-243736beef1e/08f6e420-2070-11f1-85bc-7f5c1498a248/file-jaoe38c1mmrrsqcj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>",
