      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>$\\mathrm{H}_2, \\mathrm{Pd} / \\mathrm{C}$</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The reagent that can reduce the carboxylic acid to corresponding alcohol is diborane (disassociated to $\\mathrm{BH}_3$ in ether or THF solution)</p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 18th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 5 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmqbbsmf/ef8bca32-0073-4980-93f8-ec619b0047b7/d7406280-1fa2-11f1-917e-172190bdd415/file-jaoe38c1mmqbbsmg.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmqbbsmf/ef8bca32-0073-4980-93f8-ec619b0047b7/d7406280-1fa2-11f1-917e-172190bdd415/file-jaoe38c1mmqbbsmg.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"TS EAMCET 2022 (Online) 18th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Carboxylic Acids and Its Derivatives Question 5 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mmqbbt8d/da057100-fa74-4394-88f7-e519cc09d1f1/d7b8c6d0-1fa2-11f1-917e-172190bdd415/file-jaoe38c1mmqbbt8e.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mmqbbt8d/da057100-fa74-4394-88f7-e519cc09d1f1/d7b8c6d0-1fa2-11f1-917e-172190bdd415/file-jaoe38c1mmqbbt8e.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$\\mathrm{NaBH}_4$ being weak reducing agent does not reduce carboxylic acids but reduces aldehyde and ketones.</p>\n<p>The reaction of aldehydes and ketones with zinc amalgam ( $\\mathrm{Zn} / \\mathrm{Hg}$ alloy) in concentrated hydrochloric acid, reduces the aldehyde or ketone to a hydrocarbon, is called Clemmensen reduction. It does not reduce carboxylic acid.</p>\n<p>$\\mathrm{H}_2$ over $\\mathrm{Pd} / \\mathrm{C}$ will reduce alkenes and alkynes all the way to alkanes.</p>",
